<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <title>Oliver's Portfolio</title>
    <meta
      name="description"
      content="Portfolio for Oliver Chu Barbosa, an undergraduate civil engineering student at UNSW."
    />
    <meta name="generator" content={Astro.generator} />
    <link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="/favicon.svg" />
    <link rel="icon" href="/favicon.ico" />
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/styles.css?v=2" />
  </head>
  <body>
    <header class="site-header">
      <a class="brand" href="#top" aria-label="Oliver Chu Barbosa home">
        <span>Oliver's Portfolio</span>
      </a>
      <nav aria-label="Portfolio navigation">
        <a href="#projects">Projects</a>
        <a href="#capabilities">Skills</a>
        <a href="#contact">Contact</a>
      </nav>
    </header>

    <main id="top">
      <section class="hero">
        <div class="hero-copy">
          <p class="eyebrow">Undergraduate Civil Engineering Student at UNSW</p>
          <h1>Practical design. Modelling. Analysis.</h1>
          <p class="intro">
            Clarity doesn't come from the thinking, it comes from doing.
          </p>
          <div class="hero-actions">
            <a class="button primary" href="#projects">View Projects</a>
            <a
              class="button secondary"
              href="mailto:Oliver.Chu.Barbosa@gmail.com">Email Me</a
            >
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="hero-panel" aria-label="Portfolio snapshot">
          <img
            src="/assets/portfolio-collage.jpg"
            alt="Collage of Oliver Chu Barbosa portfolio project images"
          />
          <dl>
            <div>
              <dt>4</dt>
              <dd>Major project areas</dd>
            </div>
            <div class="hero-discipline">
              <dt>
                <span>Geotechnical.</span>
                <span>Structural.</span>
                <span>Architectural.</span>
                <span>Mechanical.</span>
              </dt>
            </div>
          </dl>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section
        class="section-strip"
        id="capabilities"
        aria-labelledby="skills-title"
      >
        <div>
          <p class="eyebrow">Capabilities</p>
          <h2 id="skills-title">
            Civil engineering skills with clear technical evidence.
          </h2>
        </div>
        <ul class="skill-list">
          <li>Remediation option screening</li>
          <li>Structural calculations</li>
          <li>Revit documentation</li>
          <li>CAD modelling</li>
          <li>AS:4100, AS:3600, and AS:1684</li>
          <li>Technical reporting</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="projects" id="projects" aria-labelledby="projects-title">
        <div class="section-heading">
          <p class="eyebrow">Selected Work</p>
          <h2 id="projects-title">Projects</h2>
        </div>

        <article class="project featured">
          <div class="project-visuals">
            <p class="gallery-kicker">Take a closer look.</p>
            <div class="project-media project-gallery image-grid">
              <img
                src="/assets/pdf-images/page01_image03.png"
                alt="Contaminant plume maps for Camellia site"
                data-legend="/assets/pdf-images/page01_image02.png"
                data-legend-alt="Contaminant legend for groundwater, chloroform, carbon tetrachloride, and hexavalent chromium"
              />
              <img
                class="gallery-wide"
                src="/assets/pdf-images/page01_image04.png"
                alt="Conceptual site model for contamination exposure pathways"
                data-legend="/assets/pdf-images/page01_image05.png"
                data-legend-alt="Exposure pathway symbol legend"
              />
              <img
                src="/assets/pdf-images/page02_image01.jpg"
                alt="Hand sketch of concrete water tank geometry"
              />
              <img
                src="/assets/pdf-images/page02_image02.png"
                alt="Bored pile spacing and arrangement diagram"
              />
              <img
                src="/assets/pdf-images/page02_image03.png"
                alt="Remediation option assessment matrix"
              />
              <img
                src="/assets/pdf-images/page02_image04.png"
                alt="Foundation and soil profile diagram"
              />
              <img
                class="gallery-wide"
                src="/assets/pdf-images/page02_image05.png"
                alt="Engineering drawing for tank and site details"
              />
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="project-copy">
            <p class="project-type">Environmental and civil design</p>
            <h3>Contaminated Parramatta Light Rail Yard Solution</h3>
            <div class="three-col">
              <div>
                <h4>What</h4>
                <ul>
                  <li>
                    Designed a remediation strategy for the contaminated site in
                    Camellia, NSW, intended for a light rail stabling yard and
                    maintenance facility.
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    Designed a concrete water tank to supply future residential
                    developments and provide emergency fire support.
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    Conceptualised a detailed design of retaining walls and a
                    33-pile foundation system socketed into shale bedrock.
                  </li>
                </ul>
              </div>
              <div>
                <h4>How</h4>
                <ul>
                  <li>
                    Screened 15+ remediation technologies via FRTR guidelines
                    and cost-benefit analysis.
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    Modelled tank geometry through sketches; calculated flexural
                    capacity and added horizontal stiffeners to ensure stability
                    without thickening walls.
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    Calculated lateral earth pressures, verified wall
                    deflection, and designed 33 bored piles with end-bearing
                    into shale.
                  </li>
                </ul>
              </div>
              <div>
                <h4>Result</h4>
                <ul>
                  <li>
                    Recommended Monitored Natural Attenuation (MNA) for lowest
                    cost and minimal site disturbance.
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    Delivered a water tank with 451.7 kN/m moment capacity while
                    reducing wall thickness and construction costs.
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    Designed a pile system supporting a 48 MN vertical load with
                    settlement under 4 mm, using a hexagonal grid for even load
                    distribution.
                  </li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </article>

        <article class="project">
          <div class="project-visuals">
            <p class="gallery-kicker">Take a closer look.</p>
            <div class="project-media project-gallery">
              <img
                src="/assets/pdf-images/page03_image04.png"
                alt="Revit model of the residential complex"
              />
              <img
                src="/assets/pdf-images/page03_image01.png"
                alt="Residential house Revit front render"
              />
              <img
                src="/assets/pdf-images/page03_image02.png"
                alt="Residential kitchen Revit render"
              />
              <img
                src="/assets/pdf-images/page03_image03.png"
                alt="Formal lounge Revit render"
              />
              <img
                src="/assets/pdf-images/page03_image05.png"
                alt="Community centre Revit exterior render"
              />
              <img
                src="/assets/pdf-images/page03_image06.png"
                alt="Residential floor plan documentation"
              />
              <img
                src="/assets/pdf-images/page03_image07.png"
                alt="Revit site and documentation sheet"
              />
              <img
                src="/assets/pdf-images/page03_image08.png"
                alt="Apartment building section drawing"
              />
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="project-copy">
            <p class="project-type">Revit and construction documentation</p>
            <h3>House and Complex Revit Designs</h3>
            <div class="three-col">
              <div>
                <h4>What</h4>
                <ul>
                  <li>
                    Completed a residential house design at 10 Flinders Street,
                    including site plan, floor plans, elevations, and room
                    schedules.
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    Designed a multi-building community residential project at
                    22-25 Rothschild Ave, Rosebery, NSW.
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    Compiled Revit 2025 sheet documentation for both designs.
                  </li>
                </ul>
              </div>
              <div>
                <h4>How</h4>
                <ul>
                  <li>
                    Built 3D models of apartments and community centre using
                    Autodesk Revit.
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    Applied AS1100 material patterns and line weights for
                    construction documentation.
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    Produced cover pages, site plans, floor plans,
                    north/south/east/west elevations, sections, room schedules,
                    and quantity takeoffs.
                  </li>
                </ul>
              </div>
              <div>
                <h4>Result</h4>
                <ul>
                  <li>
                    Demonstrated proficiency in Revit worksharing, clash
                    detection, sheet management, and AS1100 drafting standards.
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    Built skills directly transferable to a trainee drafter role
                    using AutoCAD or 12D.
                  </li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </article>

        <article class="project">
          <div class="project-visuals">
            <p class="gallery-kicker">Take a closer look.</p>
            <div class="project-media project-gallery">
              <img
                src="/assets/pdf-images/page04_image03.jpg"
                alt="Morphing airfoil prototype mounted for testing"
              />
              <img
                src="/assets/pdf-images/page04_image06.png"
                alt="Completed morphing airfoil prototype"
              />
              <img
                src="/assets/pdf-images/page04_image01.png"
                alt="CAD model of NACA 0015 airfoil"
              />
              <img
                src="/assets/pdf-images/page04_image02.png"
                alt="CAD model of compliant airfoil mechanism"
              />
              <img
                src="/assets/pdf-images/page04_image04.jpg"
                alt="Wind tunnel testing setup for morphing airfoil"
              />
              <img
                src="/assets/pdf-images/page04_image05.png"
                alt="Arduino code used for airfoil testing"
              />
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="project-copy">
            <p class="project-type">Mechanical prototype and testing</p>
            <h3>Morphing Airfoil</h3>
            <div class="three-col">
              <div>
                <h4>What</h4>
                <ul>
                  <li>
                    Designed and manufactured a morphing airfoil with a
                    compliant acrylic mechanism and NACA 0015 airfoil.
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    Responsible for compliant mechanism design, leading edge
                    CAD, problem statement, and reports.
                  </li>
                </ul>
              </div>
              <div>
                <h4>How</h4>
                <ul>
                  <li>
                    Selected NACA 0015 for 15% thickness, balancing structural
                    rigidity and lift/drag ratio.
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    Used CAD tools, including extrude cut and insert curve
                    through XYZ points, to model the airfoil and compliant ribs.
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    Programmed Arduino with simple loop-based angle inputs,
                    without a manual knob, for fast testing.
                  </li>
                </ul>
              </div>
              <div>
                <h4>Result</h4>
                <ul>
                  <li>
                    Wind tunnel testing confirmed the morphed configuration
                    achieved higher lift-to-drag ratio than the non-morphed
                    configuration, validating Bernoulli's principle.
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    Delivered a lightweight, functional morphing wing tested in
                    a 300 mm x 300 mm wind tunnel with measurable lift/drag
                    data.
                  </li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </article>
      </section>

      <section class="contact" id="contact" aria-labelledby="contact-title">
        <div>
          <p class="eyebrow">Contact</p>
          <h2 id="contact-title">
